[
    {
        "content": "<p>Hi! I've been trying to write some kunit tests for my SpinLockIrq series and I've noticed that it seems like rust-analyzer stops working properly whenever <code>#[kunit_tests(…)]</code> is specified. For example:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Rust\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"cp\">#[kunit_tests(rust_spinlock)]</span>\n<span class=\"k\">mod</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nn\">tests</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">super</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"p\">;</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">use</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">crate</span><span class=\"p\">::{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">sync</span><span class=\"p\">::</span><span class=\"o\">*</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">workqueue</span><span class=\"p\">::{</span><span class=\"bp\">self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">impl_has_work</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">new_work</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">Work</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">WorkItem</span><span class=\"p\">},</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">};</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"cp\">#[pin_data]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">struct</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">IrqCondvar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"cp\">#[pin]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">value</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">SpinLockIrq</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"kt\">u32</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"cp\">#[pin]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">value_changed</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">CondVar</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"cp\">#[pin]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"n\">update_work</span><span class=\"p\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nc\">Work</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">1</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"k\">impl</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">IrqCondvar</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"k\">pub</span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"k\">crate</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">fn</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">new</span><span class=\"p\">()</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nb\">Result</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"n\">Arc</span><span class=\"o\">&lt;</span><span class=\"bp\">Self</span><span class=\"o\">&gt;&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"p\">}</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>It recognizes some of the things here, but it doesn't seem to understand that I've imported <code>CondVar</code>, <code>Work</code> or <code>Arc</code>. The moment I remove the <code>#[kunit_tests(rust_spinlock)]</code> line it starts working properly again. Is there any way I can fix this?</p>",
        "id": 521163438,
        "sender_full_name": "Lyude",
        "timestamp": 1748549533
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Have you generated a rust-project.toml file with a .config that selects <code>KCONFIG_KUNIT=y</code>?</p>",
        "id": 521163631,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1748549663
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A <code>rust-project.toml</code> file? this is the first I've heard of needing one</p>",
        "id": 521163735,
        "sender_full_name": "Lyude",
        "timestamp": 1748549713
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Don't you need to <code>make LLVM=1 rust-analyzer</code> to generate one?</p>",
        "id": 521163797,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1748549747
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>so that rust-analyzer can understand your configs</p>",
        "id": 521163818,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1748549760
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>oh you mean the rust-analyzer thing, I do have that but it's <code>KCONFIG_KUNIT=m</code> here. I assume <code>m</code> doesn't work and I need <code>y</code>?</p>",
        "id": 521163903,
        "sender_full_name": "Lyude",
        "timestamp": 1748549787
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but for kunit_tests case, not sure whether it would work because that depends on rust-analyzer can expand proc-macros</p>",
        "id": 521163939,
        "sender_full_name": "Boqun Feng",
        "timestamp": 1748549815
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>setting it to <code>y</code> worked actually!</p>",
        "id": 521164017,
        "sender_full_name": "Lyude",
        "timestamp": 1748549856
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>thank you ♥</p>",
        "id": 521164036,
        "sender_full_name": "Lyude",
        "timestamp": 1748549873
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, <code>KUNIT=y</code> is required (for them to actually run).</p>",
        "id": 521164669,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1748550145
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(The <code>#[kunit_tests]</code> can be in modules, and they will run fine as usual when loading the module, but the KUnit core itself needs to be built-in at the moment).</p>",
        "id": 521164725,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1748550169
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I should add a sentence about it to the docs (for doctests it is more obvious, since it is in the Kconfig, but for these ones it is not)</p>",
        "id": 521164986,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1748550290
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>should we have a <code>#[cfg(not(KUNIT=y))] compile_error!(\"please set KUNIT=y\")</code> to the output of <code>kunit_tests</code>?</p>",
        "id": 521165429,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1748550492
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do you mean failing the build? You are supposed to be able to disable the tests, in fact, KUnit shouldn't be enabled in production. Or do you mean something else?</p>",
        "id": 521166034,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1748550803
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>yes failing the build if tests are \"enabled\", but <code>KUNIT=m</code></p>",
        "id": 521166207,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1748550877
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't know the internals of <code>kunit_tests</code>, so it might not disable the tests if kunit is disabled</p>",
        "id": 521166297,
        "sender_full_name": "Benno Lossin",
        "timestamp": 1748550928
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't think we can fail the build if <code>KUNIT=m</code> either. Currently the tests get enabled if KUnit is enabled -- there is no way to control them \"individually\".</p>",
        "id": 521166399,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1748550978
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>(I mean in the Rust side)</p>",
        "id": 521166427,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1748550997
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>You can control them with an explicit <code>cfg</code>, and then we could fail the build if everyone does that, I guess.</p>",
        "id": 521166481,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1748551036
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>i.e. if everyone did <code>#[cfg(CONFIG_MYTESTS)] #[kunit_tests]</code>, then we could perhaps fail it they do not set <code>KUNIT=y</code>.</p>",
        "id": 521166618,
        "sender_full_name": "Miguel Ojeda",
        "timestamp": 1748551094
    }
]